defaultWritten evidence from West Midlands scrutiny Network (PEX 0006)default1.0default              defaultExecutive Summarydefault1.1
default              
defaultLocal Government Scrutiny has an integral role in the accountability framework for many services, including health and social care. The work of the Scrutiny Committees is based on the evidence
default&#xa0;
defaultand since the introduction of local government scrutiny and health scrutiny, Scrutiny Committees have built up a body of knowledge and expertise. The information provided in this memorandum is based
default&#xa0;
defaulton the work of Local Government Scrutiny across 10 West Midlands Local Authorities and will hopefully be of interest and use to the Health Select Committee in its inquiry on Public Expenditure on Health and Social Care.
default&#xa0;
default2.0default              defaultThe West Midlands Scrutiny Networkdefault2.1
default              
defaultThe West Midlands Scrutiny Network is an informal network open to all local authorities across the West Midlands. The Network aims to:
default&#xa0;
default
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultTo share experiences and knowledge and to work with other members to develop ideas and good practice which can support and strengthen overview and scrutiny in the region.
default
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultTo provide support and networking opportunities for Councillors and officers who are members of the West Midlands Network
default
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultTo represent the views of West Midlands local authorities' overview and scrutiny members at regional and national events.
default2.2
